---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy | Niirmaan Growth Hub" description="Privacy Policy for Niirmaan Growth Hub - Learn how we collect, use, and protect your data.">

  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">

    <div class="mb-10">
      <a href="/" class="text-orange-500 text-sm font-medium hover:underline">&larr; Back to Home</a>
    </div>

    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mb-10">Last updated: 2026</p>

    <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none space-y-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">

      <p>
        This Privacy Policy ("Policy") outlines how Niirmaan Growth Hub ("we," "us," "our") collects, uses, handles, and processes the data you provide while using our website, products, or services. By using this website or availing our goods or services, you agree to the terms of this Policy and consent to our use, storage, disclosure, and transfer of your information as described herein.
      </p>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Business Description</h2>
        <p>
          Niirmaan Growth Hub is a business coaching and consulting firm based in Mumbai, dedicated to empowering women to launch and grow their businesses. We provide end-to-end support, from brand creation to go-to-market strategies. Our services include business coaching, marketing strategy, sales strategy, and business development for women entrepreneurs.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Commitment to Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          We are committed to protecting your privacy in accordance with applicable laws and regulations. This Policy explains how we handle your data and ensures transparency in our practices. We encourage you to read this Policy carefully to understand how your information is being processed.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Niirmaan Growth Hub may update this Policy periodically. We urge you to check this page regularly to stay informed about the latest version of the Policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">What Data We Collect</h2>
        <p>We may collect the following information from you:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-3 space-y-1">
          <li>Name</li>
          <li>Contact Information (including address, email address, and phone number)</li>
          <li>Demographic Information (such as preferences or interests)</li>
          <li>Personal Data or other information relevant to providing our goods or services to you</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-500">Note: The term "Personal Data" is defined under relevant Indian laws.</p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We do not store credit card, debit card, or similar payment data. All data collected is in strict compliance with applicable laws and guidelines.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">How We Use Your Data</h2>
        <p>We use the data we collect for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-3 space-y-1">
          <li>Internal Record Keeping</li>
          <li>Improving Our Products and Services</li>
          <li>Providing Updates about our products, services, and special offers</li>
          <li>Communicating Information to you</li>
          <li>Internal Training and Quality Assurance</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Who We Share Your Data With</h2>
        <p>We may share your information with:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-3 space-y-1">
          <li>Third-Party Service Providers to facilitate the provision of goods or services, respond to your queries, fulfill orders, or for other operational and business purposes</li>
          <li>Group Companies (to the extent relevant)</li>
          <li>Auditors or Advisors as required for their services</li>
          <li>Governmental or Regulatory Authorities to comply with legal obligations or regulatory requirements</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Use of Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          We use cookies to collect information and better understand customer behavior. You can instruct your browser to refuse cookies or notify you when a cookie is being sent. However, refusing cookies may limit your ability to fully avail our goods or services.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We do not control the use of cookies by third parties. Third-party service providers have their own privacy policies addressing how they use such information.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Your Rights Relating to Your Data</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Right to Review:</strong> You can review the data you have provided and request corrections or amendments (to the extent feasible). However, we are not responsible for the authenticity of the data you provide.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          <strong>Withdrawal of Consent:</strong> You can choose not to provide your data or withdraw your consent at any time by writing to us. Please note that withdrawing consent may affect our ability to provide you with our goods or services.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-500">Note: These rights are subject to compliance with applicable laws.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Data Retention</h2>
        <p>We retain your information:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-3 space-y-1">
          <li>For as long as we are providing goods or services to you</li>
          <li>As permitted under applicable law, we may retain your data even after you terminate your business relationship with us. However, such data will be processed in accordance with applicable laws and this Policy</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Data Security</h2>
        <p>
          We use commercially reasonable and legally required precautions to protect the integrity and security of your information.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Queries / Grievance Officer</h2>
        <p>For any questions, concerns, or grievances regarding this Policy, please contact us:</p>
        <div class="mt-4 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-5 space-y-1">
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Niirmaan Growth Hub</p>
          <p>Email: <a href="mailto:letsconnect@niirmaangrowthhub.com" class="text-orange-500 hover:underline">letsconnect@niirmaangrowthhub.com</a></p>
          <p>Phone: <a href="tel:+919167745588" class="text-orange-500 hover:underline">+91 91677 45588</a></p>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>

  </main>

</BaseLayout>
